klradial                              macro                             klradial

NAME
     kkllrraaddiiaall - scan along a radius in the KKLL-plane in reciprocal space

SYNOPSIS

     kkllrraaddiiaall aannggllee ssttaarrtt eenndd iinntteerrvvaallss ttiimmee [[eexxpprreessssiioonn]]

DESCRIPTION

     The kkllrraaddiiaall macro scans along a radius in the KKLL-plane in reciprocal
     space.  The angle of the arc from the positive KK axis is given by aannggllee and
     the scan runs from the radius given by ssttaarrtt to the radius given by eenndd.
     The number of data points collected will be iinntteerrvvaallss++11.  Count time is
     given by ttiimmee, which if positive, specifies seconds and if negative,
     specifies monitor counts.

     The optional last argument can supply expressions to be evaluated after KK
     and LL are calculated for each point.  You may, for example, supply an
     expression to calculate values for HH or include expressions to offset the
     values of KK and LL.

EXAMPLES

     kkllrraaddiiaall 4455 ..00 ssqqrrtt((22)) 1100 1100
     kkllrraaddiiaall 9900 00 11 2200 6600 ""KK++==..55;; LL++==..55""

